comments.LineComment: | The heart of the L-system visualization: expressing expansion and
| An L-system rendering is a textbook hylomorphism:
|   data → unfold (ana) → intermediate structure → fold (cata) → result
|   seed → expand rules → expanded string → interpret turtle → segments
| For lazy/infinite generation, we use an apomorphism - an unfold that
| can terminate early by providing a pre-computed result:
|   apo :: (a → f (Either (Fix f) a)) → a → Fix f
|   - Left (Fix f): stop here with this result
| This lets us stop expanding when the viewport is filled.
